definitions.definition: An airliner capable of seating seven or more passengers in a single row of economy seating, with two aisles or more.
examples: The world airline fleet of long-range aircraft consists almost entirely of widebodies .

definitions.definition: A player with a wide or heavyset body.
A tennis racket having a thick (although not necessarily wide ) frame, increasing the racket's stiffness .
